        "description": "Lit the Light Trust is a registered Nonprofit organization exclusively working for the betterment of visually impaired persons, It is a volunteer-driven organization involving youth volunteerism more than 2000+ volunteers are engaged every year for helping visually challenged people in Scribing, Audio recording, Identifying Hidden talents & promoting special skills, Inclusive job placement and career development.\n\n\n**It was the vision of a single person, S.N. Barath**, that sparked this endeavor. After attending reading sessions for a year, a visually impaired student of Government High School in Poonamalle scored 960 in his class 12 board examination. This was an eye-opener for Barath. He now realised that a little help could go a long way in helping such students.\n\nIn 2014, along with a few of his colleagues **RamKumar & Ravikant** joined hands in this journey of social Service. Lit the Light **formed as a volunteer group from 26th Jan, 2014.** This organization is actively involved in the empowerment of the Visually Impaired. Officially registered as charitable trust with Tamilnadu Government in **2017.**",
