            "description": "Despite being highly capable, the blind and visually impaired are often overlooked by hiring managers and business owners. Lit the Light initiates career assistance for the visually challenged job seekers, who approach us. We support them few vital needs such as writing or modifying their resume. Since resume is the first impression with a potential employer. Next comes the preparation for the interview, to build up the confidence to face the interview process through appropriate counseling. The do’s and don’ts of applying for a job. Where to look for work that’s right for the candidate’s experience and interest. All these vital services are provided to our visually challenged candidates or job seekers by our well-qualified volunteers. Basic assistance or mentoring is provided to our candidates in exploring possible career choices and to understand the basics of job seeking, including the resume and interview process.\n\nLit the Light acknowledges the time and expertise provided by our dedicated group volunteers and the leads **Ms Pavithra and Ms. Swathi** who ensure our candidates are placed better to face the world independently.",
