            "isActive": true,
            "description": "Talent needs recognition and appreciation. Able, eager visually challenged want to be known for talents, work; now it's up to us to support them to achieve their goals. Lit the Light has a dedicated team of volunteers whose prime focus is to recognize the hidden talents of our visually challenged people from all age groups.  Visually Challenged also have different talents like singing, playing musical instruments, dancing, and many excel in various sports like cricket, volleyball kind of team sports as well as individual sports like Judo, Karate, etc. and some partial sighted are good at sketching and drawing as well. Lit the Light has been working hard to encourage these talents. We try our best to bring them into limelight, have sponsored many sports team, who have achieved on national level too. we have a dedicated team which takes care of unearthing these talents in them. We   make a video of our musical talents and share it on social media and try to get recognition for their talents. Lit the Light wishes to appreciate our Talent Hunt leads for their untiring support and all the others for helping us to be strong in our mission.",
